===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{astronomy}}, {{astrology}} Half of the [[celestial sphere]], as divided by either the [[ecliptic]] or the [[celestial equator]]  {{defdate|from 14th c.}}.
# {{figuratively}}  A realm or domain of activity  {{defdate|1503}}.
# {{geography}} Half of the [[Earth]], such as the [[Northern Hemisphere]], [[Southern Hemisphere]], [[Western Hemisphere]] or [[Eastern Hemisphere]], [[Land Hemisphere]], [[Water Hemisphere]] etc.  {{defdate|1550s}}.
# {{geometry}} Any half-[[sphere]], formed by a [[plane]] [[intersect]]ing the center of a sphere.  {{defdate|1580s}}.
# {{cartography}} A map or projection of a celestial or terrestrial hemisphere  {{defdate|1706}}.
# {{anatomy}} Either of the two [[halves]] of the [[cerebrum]]. {{defdate|1804}}.

